P2PDSNP.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT({+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ)
* TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ)  HILITE(USCORE)
# TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  SKIP(ON)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
@ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ)
< AREA(SCRL)   EXTEND(ON)
)BODY EXPAND(??)
@?-?&p2pverno - Dataset Names and Display Options?-?
¬COMMAND ===>*zcmd                                                             #
<MYAREA -----------------------------------------------------------------------<
)AREA MYAREA
¬          Left-Side DSN{==>$dsnl                                          #
¬ Member Name or Pattern{==>$mbrleft #
¬      Incl/Excl Members{==>$z#      ¬(I=Include   X=Exclude)
¬                 VOLSER{==>$volidl# ¬(for uncataloged datasets)
+
¬         Right-side DSN{==>$dsnr                                          #
¬ Member Name or Pattern{==>$mbrrite #
¬      Incl/Excl Members{==>$z#      ¬(I=Include   X=Exclude)
¬                 VOLSER{==>$volidr# ¬(for uncataloged datasets)
+
¬    Enter "/" to select an option - Leave options blank to process all members
+
¬   *Z#¬Display only if member names match
¬   *Z#¬Display only if member names and stats match
¬   *Z#¬Display only if member names match but stats don't match
¬   *Z#¬Display only if member names are different
¬   *Z#¬Show only the members unique to the left-side dataset
¬   *Z#¬Show only the members unique to the right-side dataset
¬   *Z#¬Show members on left that are older than members on right
¬   *Z#¬Show members on right that are older than members on left
)INIT
 &ZHTOP = P2P00000
 .HELP  = P2P00000
 .ZVARS = '(MASKOPTL MASKOPTR NAMESAME STATSAME STATDIFF NAMEDIFF UNIQLEFT  +
            UNIQRITE OLDRLEFT OLDRRITE)'
)PROC
VER (&DSNL,NONBLANK)
VER (&MASKOPTL,LIST,I,X,' ',MSG=PTPM001)
VER (&DSNR,NONBLANK)
VER (&MASKOPTR,LIST,I,X,' ',MSG=PTPM001)
VER (&NAMESAME,LIST,/,' ',MSG=PTPM002)
VER (&STATSAME,LIST,/,' ',MSG=PTPM002)
VER (&STATDIFF,LIST,/,' ',MSG=PTPM002)
VER (&NAMEDIFF,LIST,/,' ',MSG=PTPM002)
VER (&UNIQLEFT,LIST,/,' ',MSG=PTPM002)
VER (&UNIQRITE,LIST,/,' ',MSG=PTPM002)
VER (&OLDRLEFT,LIST,/,' ',MSG=PTPM002)
VER (&OLDRRITE,LIST,/,' ',MSG=PTPM002)
&PFKPRESD = .PFKEY
)HELP
FIELD(dsnl)       PANEL(P2P11000)
FIELD(mbrleft)    PANEL(P2P11000)
FIELD(maskoptl)   PANEL(P2P11000)
FIELD(volidl)     PANEL(P2P11000)
FIELD(dsnr)       PANEL(P2P12000)
FIELD(mbrrite)    PANEL(P2P12000)
FIELD(maskoptr)   PANEL(P2P12000)
FIELD(volidr)     PANEL(P2P12000)
FIELD(namesame)   PANEL(P2P13010)
FIELD(statsame)   PANEL(P2P13020)
FIELD(statdiff)   PANEL(P2P13030)
FIELD(namediff)   PANEL(P2P13040)
FIELD(uniqleft)   PANEL(P2P13050)
FIELD(uniqrite)   PANEL(P2P13060)
FIELD(oldrleft)   PANEL(P2P13070)
FIELD(oldrrite)   PANEL(P2P13080)
)END

%COMMAND ===>_zcmd                                            %SCROLL ===>_amt #

&dtl1
&dtl2
&dtl3
&dtl4
&dtl5
&dtl6
&dtl7

FIELD(gcmdr)       PANEL(P2P23000)

P2P00000.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
)BODY CMD(ZCMD) EXPAND(ÝÝ)
+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
+
+                         ---------------------------
+                         |   GENERAL INFORMATION   |
+                         ---------------------------
¬
¬  PD2PDS is composed of two main panels: the Dataset Name and Display
¬  Options panel and the Member List panel. When PDS2PDS is invoked the
¬  Dataset Name panel is displayed. Enter the two dataset names and
¬  desired options then press the ENTER key. The Member List panel will
¬  then be displayed.
¬
¬  The following topics are presented in sequence,
¬  or may be selected by number:
¬
¬
@   1¬- The Dataset Name and Display Options panel
@   2¬- The Member List panel
¬
¬
¬
)INIT
  &ZHTOP = P2P00000
)PROC
  &zsel = TRANS(&zcmd
                1,P2P10000
                2,P2P20000
                )
)END

P2P10000.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
)BODY EXPAND(ÝÝ)
+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
+
+                 ------------------------------------------
+                 | Dataset Name and Display Options panel |
+                 ------------------------------------------
¬
¬  In this panel you enter the names of the two datasets whose members
¬  you want to see listed.
¬
¬  The members of the Left-Side Dataset Name will be displayed on
¬  the left side of the Member List Panel and the members of the Right-
¬  Side Dataset Name will be displayed on the right side of the Member
¬  List panel.
¬
¬  The following topics are presented in sequence,
¬  or may be selected by number:
¬
@   1¬- The Left-Side Dataset Name Fields
@   2¬- The Right-Side Dataset Name Fields
@   3¬- The Member Display Options
¬
)INIT
  &ZHTOP = P2P00000
)PROC
  &zsel = TRANS(&zcmd
                1,P2P11000
                2,P2P12000
                3,P2P13000
                )
)END

P2P11000.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
)BODY EXPAND(ÝÝ)
+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
+
+                      ---------------------------------
+                      | Left-Side Dataset Name Fields |
+                      ---------------------------------
¬
¬  In this set of fields you enter the dataset name, member name, and
¬  Include/Exclude field for the dataset members that will appear on
¬  the left side of the Member List Panel.
¬
¬  The dataset name may be entered with or without quotes. If entered
¬  without quotes then it will be considered a partially qualified name
¬  and will be prefixed with your TSO PREFIX value.
¬
¬  If your TSO PREFIX is not set, then the dataset name will be used
¬  as is.
¬
¬  In the member name field you may enter an exact member name or a
¬
¬
¬                                                          @(continued)
)INIT
)PROC
  &zcont = P2P11010
)END

P2P11010.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
)BODY EXPAND(ÝÝ)
+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
¬
¬  pattern. If you enter a full name, only that member will be
¬  selected for processing. If you enter a member name pattern, only
¬  members matching the pattern will be selected for processing.
¬
¬  You can use either an asterisk or a percent sign as a wildcard in
¬  the pattern.
¬
¬  Entering ABC* as the member name pattern would give you all members
¬  that begin with the letters 'ABC'.
¬
¬  Entering ABC%DE would give you all 6-character names whose first
¬  three letters are 'ABC' and whose last two letters are 'DE'. The '%'
¬  is a single-position wildcard.
¬
¬  Entering an 'I' in the Include/Exclude field tells PDS2PDS to
¬  select only those members that match the specified member name
¬  pattern. Only these members will be shown on the Member List panel.
¬
¬                                                          @(continued)
)INIT
)PROC
  &zcont = P2P11020
)END

P2P11020.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
)BODY EXPAND(ÝÝ)
+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
¬
¬  Entering an 'X' in the Include/Exclude field tells PDS2PDS to
¬  exclude those members that match the member name pattern. Excluded
¬  members are not shown on the Member List panel.
¬
¬  If you enter a member name pattern but leave the Include/Exclude
¬  field blank, all pds members will be processed.
¬
¬  If you enter either an I or an X in the Include/Exclude field but
¬  leave the member name pattern blank, all dataset members will be
¬  processed.
¬
¬  The VOLSER field is where you enter the name of the DASD volume where
¬  the dataset resides. You should only use this field for uncataloged
¬  datasets.
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
)INIT
)PROC
)END

P2P13000.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
)BODY EXPAND(ÝÝ)
+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
+
+                      --------------------------------
+                      |    Member Display Options    |
+                      --------------------------------
¬
¬  The Member Display options allow you to display only those members that match
¬  certain criteria. Only one Display Option may be selected at a time.
¬
¬  1¬- Display only if member names match
¬  2¬- Display only if member names and stats match
¬  3¬- Display only if member names match but stats don't match
¬  4¬- Display only if member names are different
¬  5¬- Show only the members unique to the left-side dataset
¬  6¬- Show only the members unique to the right-side dataset
¬  7¬- Show members on left that are older than members on right
¬  8¬- Show members on right that are older than members on left
¬
¬
¬
¬
)INIT
  &ZHTOP = P2P00000
)PROC
  &zsel = TRANS(&zcmd
                1,P2P13010
                2,P2P13020
                3,P2P13030
                4,P2P13040
                5,P2P13050
                6,P2P13060
                7,P2P13070
                8,P2P13080
                )
)END

$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)

P2P13020.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
* TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ)
)BODY EXPAND(ÝÝ)
+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
¬
*  Display only if member names and stats match
¬
¬     This option will display a pds member only if the name appears
¬     in both partitioned datasets, AND the statistics for each member
¬     are exactly the same.
¬
¬     Members that appear only in one pds or the other will not be
¬     displayed and members that appear in both datasets but whose
¬     statistics are different will not be displayed.
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬

¬
¬
¬
)INIT
)PROC
)END

¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +

¬
¬     This option will display a pds member only if it exists in the
¬     right-side dataset AND NOT in the left-side dataset.
¬
¬     Members that appear in both datasets are not displayed and
¬     members that appear only in the left-side dataset are not
¬     displayed.
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
)INIT
)PROC
)END

P2P20000.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)

)BODY EXPAND(ÝÝ)
+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
+
+                         ---------------------------
+                         |    Member List Panel    |
+                         ---------------------------
¬
¬  Most of the work in PDS2PDS is done from the Member List Panel,
¬  for which there are four types of commands.
¬
¬  The following topics are presented in sequence,
¬  or may be selected by number:
¬
@   1¬- Primary Commands
@   2¬- Confirm Line Command
@   3¬- Global Commands
@   4¬- Line Commands
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
)INIT
)PROC
  &zsel = TRANS(&zcmd
                1,P2P21000
                2,P2P22000
                3,P2P23000
                4,P2P24000
                )
)END

P2P21000.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)

+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
+
+                         ---------------------------
+                         |    Primary Commands     |
+                         ---------------------------
¬
¬  Primary Commands are entered from the ISPF command line.
¬
¬  The following topics are presented in sequence,
¬  or may be selected by number:
¬
@   1¬- The LOCate Command
@   2¬- The REFresh Command
@   3¬- The FLip Command
@   4¬- The LF Command
@   5¬- The RI Command
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
)INIT
)PROC
  &zsel = TRANS(&zcmd
                1,P2P21010
                2,P2P21020
                3,P2P21030
                4,P2P21040
                5,P2P21050
                )
)END

P2P21010.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
)BODY EXPAND(ÝÝ)
+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
¬
¬  The LOCate Command
¬
¬    Format: LOCate membername
¬
¬    The LOCate command will position the member list display so that
¬    the specified member name is on the first line of the list.
¬
¬    If the specified member does not exist the display will be
¬    posititioned to the name that most closely matches the specified
¬    name.
¬
¬    LOCATE may be abbreviated as L or LOC.
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
)INIT
)PROC
)END

P2P21020.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
)BODY EXPAND(ÝÝ)
+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
¬
¬  The REFresh Command
¬
¬    Format: REFresh
¬
¬    Often after deleting and copying members from one pds to the other
¬    the member list gets out of order.
¬
¬    The REFresh command will rebuild the member list display and resort
¬    the members of both datasets into the proper order.
¬
¬    REFresh may be abbreviated as R or REF.
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
)INIT
)PROC
)END

P2P21030.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)

)BODY EXPAND(ÝÝ)

¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
¬
¬  The FLip Command
¬
¬    Format: FLip
¬
¬    The FLip command will move the left-side member list to the right
¬    side and vice versa.
¬
¬    FLip may be abbreviated as FL.
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
)INIT
)PROC
)END

P2P21040.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
)BODY EXPAND(ÝÝ)
+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
¬
¬  The LF Command
¬
¬    Format: LF (no abbreviation for this command)
¬
¬    There is only room in the Member List panel to show three or four
¬    statistics fields at once. The LF command moves the display of
¬    member statistics one field to the left each time the command is
¬    entered.
¬
¬    The order of fields is: vv.mm, Created, Changed, Time, Size, Init,
¬                            Mod, User, amd Alias.
¬
¬    If the Created, Changed, and Time fields are showing, the LF
¬    command would shift the display to the left so that the vv.mm,
¬    Created, and Changed fields were showing.
¬
¬
¬
¬
)INIT
)PROC
)END

P2P21050.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)

+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
¬
¬  The RI Command
¬
¬    Format: RI (no abbreviation for this command)
¬
¬    There is only room in the Member List panel to show three or four
¬    statistics fields at once. The RI command moves the display of
¬    member statistics one field to the right each time the command is
¬    entered.
¬
¬    The order of fields is: vv.mm, Created, Changed, Time, Size, Init,
¬                            Mod, User, amd Alias.
¬
¬    If the Created, Changed, and Time fields are showing, the RI
¬    command would shift the display to the right so that the Changed,
¬    Time, and Size fields were showing.
¬
¬
¬
¬
)INIT
)PROC
)END

P2P22000.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
)BODY EXPAND(ÝÝ)
+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
+
+                         ---------------------------
+                         |   Confirm Line Command  |
+                         ---------------------------
¬
¬  The Confirm Line Command fields provide a way to prevent the
¬  accidental deleting, renaming, or moving of members during the
¬  execution of line commands.
¬
¬  The Confirm Line Command options are in effect for the Copy, Delete,
¬  Move, and Rename commands. They are not in effect for the Edit,
¬  Browse, View, Show All Stats, or SuperCe commands since these commands
¬  do not automatically change either dataset.
¬
¬  Valid values for these fields are Y, N, or blank. If the fields
¬  contain N or blank no command confirmation is done.
¬
¬  If either field contains 'Y' a panel is displayed asking you to
¬  confirm the command.
¬
)INIT
)PROC
)END

P2P23010.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
)BODY EXPAND(ÝÝ)
+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
¬
¬  Global Command 'C' - Copy members from one pds to the other
¬
¬      After the command is entered a pop-up panel appears.
¬
¬      To bypass copying the current member, press PF3. This will take
¬      you to the next member.
¬
¬      Press the ENTER key to copy the member to the other pds.
¬
¬      Select 'Replace like-named members' to replace existing members
¬      in the target pds.
¬
¬      Select 'Set member copy confirmation off' to copy all members to
¬      the target pds without confirming each member copy individually.
¬
¬      Select 'Cancel member copy and return to previous screen' to stop
¬      the copy process altogether and return to the member list panel.
¬
¬
)INIT
)PROC
)END

P2P23110.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)

)BODY EXPAND(ÝÝ)
+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
¬
¬  Global Command 'SC' - Invoke SuperCe for both datasets
¬
¬      This command will compare matching members in both datasets.  Members
¬      that appear only in one dataset or the other are not selected for
¬      comparison.
¬
¬      This command will take you to the SuperCe panel (ISPF Option 3.15). If
¬      you did not enter the VOLSER for the dataset on the dataset name panel,
¬      the dataset names will be filled in for you on the SuperCe panel.
¬
¬      If you did fill in the VOLSER field for one of the datasets then that
¬      dataset name will be blank on the SuperCe panel. Just press ENTER on the
¬      SuperCe panel to proceed to the next panel, which is where you will enter
¬      the uncataloged DSN and VOLSER.
¬
¬      Once the SuperCe screen appears you can set or change any of the SuperCe
¬      commands or options just as if you had entered SuperCe through the
¬      regular ISPF menu.
¬
)INIT
)PROC
)END

P2P23120.text:

¬

¬      each member, total them up, and show the results in a pop-up
¬      panel.
¬
¬      This command only counts lines for those members that have
¬      statistics. Members without statistics are not counted in the
¬      total. For this information to be accurate for all members of
¬      the datasets, all members must have statics showing.
¬
¬      Press PF3 to exit the pop-up panel and return to the Member List
¬      Panel.
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
)INIT
)PROC
)END

P2P24030.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
)BODY EXPAND(ÝÝ)
+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
¬
¬  Line Command 'D' - Delete a member from one pds
¬
¬      This command immediately deletes the member from the pds.
¬
¬      If you want command confirmation for line commands enter a 'Y'
¬      into the Confirm Line Command field for this pds.
¬
¬      See the tutorial panel for the Global Delete command for details
¬      of command confirmation.
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
)INIT
)PROC
)END

P2P24040.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
)BODY EXPAND(ÝÝ)
+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
¬
¬  Line Command 'R' - Rename a member of a pds
¬
¬      After the command is entered a pop-up panel appears.
¬
¬      To bypass renaming the current member, press PF3. This will
¬      return you to the member list panel.
¬
¬      Enter a new member name and press the ENTER key to rename the
¬      member.
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
)INIT
)PROC
)END

P2P24090.text:
)ATTR DEFAULT(@+_)
$ TYPE(INPUT)  INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(TURQ) HILITE(USCORE)
¬ TYPE(TEXT)   INTENS(LOW)  COLOR(GREEN)
)BODY EXPAND(ÝÝ)
+Ý-Ý&p2pverno Primary HelpÝ-Ý
¬OPTION  ===>$zcmd                                                             +
¬
¬  Line Command 'SC' - Invoke SuperCe for both members
¬
¬      This command will take you to the SuperCe panel (ISPF Option
¬      3.15). The dataset name and SuperCe statements dataset name
¬      will be filled in for you.
¬
¬      From this point you can use SuperCe as always. You can set the
¬      Processing Options that you want and you can edit the statements
¬      dataset and modify it to your liking.
¬
¬      After you're finished with SuperCe just press PF3 to return to
¬      the PDS2PDS Member List Panel.
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
¬
)INIT
)PROC
)END
